<spell>
  <name>Unraveling Whisper</name>
  <source>TCM</source>
  <level>2</level>
  <concentration></concentration>
  <school>Enchantment</school>
  <time>1 action</time>
  <range>30 ft</range>
  <components>V,S</components>
  <duration>1 round</duration>
  <classes>Bard, Sorcerer, Warlock, Wizard</classes>
  <text>Choose a creature you can see within range and whisper a frightful phrase that only the target can hear. The target must make a Wisdom saving throw. On a failed save, the target takes 2d6 Psychic damage and has the Frightened condition until the start of your next turn. On a successful save, the target takes half as much damage only. While Frightened in this way, the creature has Vulnerability to your choice of Bludgeoning, Piercing, or Slashing damage.</text>
  <hltext>You can target one additional creature for each spell slot level above 2.</hltext>
</spell>

<spell>
